				\begin{document}$$\bar{1}$$\end{document}0} and {11¯\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\bar{1}$$\end{document}00} facets and the root cause for the inertness of basal {0001} facets. In addition, the influence of oxygen vacancies is investigated. Our work aims to provide experimental evidence for controversial active site determination and to set a basis for understanding facet-depending activities of hydroxides-based OER catalysts.

